      Snehaanchal envisions that nobody must live with or die in pain of any sort; physical, psychosocial or emotional.
      Though cure may not be always possible, care can be endless. To ensure this vision is materialized, creating
      awareness
      about Palliative Care and to make it available and accessible to all, especially the poor, is paramount.
      <br />
      Our Awareness & Advocacy team regularly undertakes the following initiatives.
    </p>

    <ol style="font-size: 1.1em">
      <li>
        Talks and Presentations are done at Schools, Colleges, Offices, Clubs, Industries and Social or Community Forums
        like
        Senior Citizen’s Forum, Housing Society Group, etc.
      </li>
      <li>
        Home visits are made in slums of Nagpur City with the assistance of Anganwadi/Asha workers to spread the message
        of
        Palliative Care and its easy and free availability.
      </li>
      <li>Talk shows on the subject are periodically done on Radio Akashwani and on local TV channels of Nagpur.</li>
